  "prompt": "What are some tips for getting hired at Blizzard Entertainment?",
  "response": "Here are some tips for getting hired at Blizzard Entertainment:\n\n1. Technical Skills\n- Have strong programming, design, or art skills\n- Be proficient in relevant game development tools\n- Keep your portfolio updated with high-quality work\n\n2. Education\n- Consider a degree in game design, computer science, digital arts, or a related field\n- Many Blizzard employees have technical or creative backgrounds\n\n3. Knowledge of Blizzard Games\n- Be familiar with their game franchises like World of Warcraft, Overwatch, Diablo, StarCraft\n- Show genuine passion for their games and game development\n\n4. Networking\n- Attend gaming conferences and industry events\n- Connect with Blizzard employees on LinkedIn\n- Participate in game development communities\n\n5. Internships\n- Apply for internship opportunities at Blizzard\n- Gain experience that could lead to full-time employment\n\n6. Entry Points\n- Consider starting in QA (quality assurance) or testing roles\n- Look for junior or entry-level positions\n\n7. Application Process\n- Tailor your resume and cover letter to specific roles\n- Highlight relevant skills and experiences\n- Demonstrate creativity and problem-solving abilities\n\nRemember that competition is high, so stand out with exceptional skills and enthusiasm.",
